  "text": "It is always a challenge for a laboratory to improve tests in conditions that are essentially clinical diagnoses. Such is the case with ocular toxoplasmosis. Established dogma is that active ocular toxoplasmosis and the value of the dye test do not correlate. [CITATION_1] While our previous results [CITATION_2] showed this to be incorrect, our current results show significant diVerences in the immunoblot patterns seen with sera from patients with ocular toxoplasmosis compared with sera from patients with other causes of their eye disease (p < 0.001).",
